questions. Overwhelmingly, the students

25:30.721 --> 25:32.806
approved. We're having a faculty meeting in the 
old chemistry lecture of arts and sciences And

25:39.773 --> 25:44.658
your dad, as was his pattern, would speak to each of 
the college faculties once a year. And this was

25:44.758 --> 25:48.282
Arts and Sciences Day. And so we were not going to 
have a faculty referendum. And we faculty were

25:52.427 --> 25:54.429
really uptight about that. You know, why in the 
world? And in his remarks, he didn't say a single

25:56.331 --> 26:01.757
thing about faculty referendum. So there were 
questions and answers. And they said, OK, now

26:03.639 --> 26:06.102
there's time for one more question. I'm sitting in 
the next to back row, and I raise my hand, and I think

26:06.942 --> 26:18.538
it was Cooper recognized, and I stood up, and I was 
so frightened that my voice quivered. And I said,

26:19.399 --> 26:24.746
you know, Mr. President, there's a referendum 
tomorrow for students. Why aren't you having a

26:24.766 --> 26:27.189
faculty referendum? And he then chuckled and 
said, hell, I don't need to have a faculty

26:27.209 --> 26:30.734
referendum. I know y'all are all in favor of these 
things. Everybody said, oh, yeah, yeah, yeah,

26:33.017 --> 26:35.380
meeting adjourned. And as we walked out, most of my 
buddies walked by and said, where are you working

26:36.136 --> 26:40.480
next year? Well, now we're about seven, eight 
years later. This is the last session I ever had

26:46.847 --> 26:48.949
with your dad. And I was in there begging for more 
money for the library, as chairman of the library

26:49.089 --> 26:53.794
committee. And in the end of the conversation, I 
said, do you remember that question I asked you

26:53.814 --> 26:58.219
that day? And he said, yes. And I remember how 
frightened you were. I was dumbfounded that his

27:03.423 --> 27:07.827
memory was that sharp. Also, I want to mention to 
you, in that conversation, I then said... He

27:12.411 --> 27:13.212
really had. He really had. I don't care how gruff he 
had to be to get stuff done, he did have such a tender

27:14.974 --> 27:19.618
heart. And you see, some of us didn't know that for a 
while. And I said, we're talking about all these

27:23.342 --> 27:25.444
changes. I said, only you could have done it. And he 
said, what do you mean? Now, by this time, you know

27:28.006 --> 27:32.130
how you kind of sometimes sit around... And he 
said, what do you mean? I said, well, sir, they

27:35.408 --> 27:52.467
couldn't say you weren't a Texan, that you weren't 
an Aggie, that you hadn't been in the Corps, that

27:35.408 --> 27:52.467
you hadn't served your country, that you didn't 
work hard, that you didn't have a strong personal

27:35.408 --> 27:52.467
private life, that, you know, there wasn't any 
gossip or anything out there. They couldn't say

27:52.827 --> 28:02.758
you didn't know your way around Austin and that you 
weren't acquainted with people named Connelly

27:52.827 --> 28:02.758
and Johnson and Teague and Pickle and things like 
that. and that you were one of those fuddy-duddy

28:03.262 --> 28:08.327
PhDs from somewhere way off. He leaned back and he 
said, oh, I never thought about any of that. I said,

28:11.550 --> 28:13.552
oh, I'm sure you didn't. Well, by then he was 
chocolate.

28:21.020 --> 28:29.148
And did you sense in him satisfaction that 
progress was being made in the 60s? No. You have to

28:29.671 --> 28:32.996
remember, too, I finished high school in 1960. I 
went three years to Austin and finished there. I

28:38.044 --> 28:41.189
taught two years in Houston, and then I went to 
Massachusetts. I taught there, and then I moved to

28:41.249 --> 28:43.212
Michigan. But by then, the enrollment was going. 
So my contact, especially after the mid-'60s,

28:45.375 --> 28:54.750
you didn't call like we do now. We sure didn't 
travel like we do now. So I really missed a lot of

28:58.604 --> 29:02.328
that. And A&M was really, really making great 
progress during those days. One of the big deals

29:11.838 --> 29:21.868
when I was teaching in Newton, Massachusetts, was 
Dad was going to be on, I think it was the Today Show,

29:11.838 --> 29:21.868
and was going to be interviewed by Sandra Van Oker. 
And my principal made arrangements to have a TV so

29:21.983 --> 29:29.272
that I could watch Dad on national television. And 
I've got a feeling that his confidence of doing

29:30.214 --> 29:39.826
that was about where yours was, asking that 
question. He was so ill at ease. Alright, now, what

29:43.411 --> 29:51.501
do you think of his

29:43.411 --> 29:51.501
duties until the Which part of his duties do you 
think he enjoyed most and enjoyed least? Most he

29:57.451 --> 29:58.913
probably enjoyed the students. Okay. Like he 
didn't enjoy speech making? No. He didn't enjoy

30:03.359 --> 30:05.261
speech making. What about going to Austin and 
Washington to work directly with the key leaders?

30:11.049 --> 30:11.750
Did he enjoy that? You know, I never remember Dad 
complaining about anything that he had. You know,

30:21.822 --> 30:26.408
I never remember regrets.

30:27.509 --> 30:33.056
I never remember spoken

30:27.509 --> 30:33.056
hate that just wasn't in his name. If it was the job, 
you did it. And I think I inherited that from him. I

30:38.403 --> 30:40.086
think my kids have inherited that. You know, you 
just... Life doesn't come to you on a platter. And

30:45.172 --> 30:48.677
you just... Whatever the job is, you do it. I have 
the impression that... And I think one day he kind

30:52.079 --> 30:58.185
of referred to this in a brief conversation. I have 
the impression that Governor John Connolly would

30:58.966 --> 31:09.236
sometimes chat directly with your dad about 
suggested board appointments. I can remember

31:10.598 --> 31:14.942
when I was in Austin that dad would come and meet 
with Governor Connolly. And I remember getting to

31:14.962 --> 31:21.529
go pick dad up one day and getting introduced to 
Governor Connolly and just being so charmed. But

31:22.133 --> 31:32.830
for dad to then turn around and tell me at lunch what 
they talked about just was not his nature. Because

31:33.151 --> 31:39.561
I have the impression that even the problems too, 
that he kept those inside. I assume. I assume.

